-- Man Dies From Plague in Gansu Province After Eating Marmot, Xinhua Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-16T00:00:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/man-dies-from-plague-in-gansu-province-after-eating-marmot-xinhua-says.html

          
          
             A 41-year-old man died of endemic
rural plague in northern China’s Gansu province after eating a
marmot he caught at a construction site, the provincial
government said.  
 The town in Jiuquan city was quarantined, according to a
statement on the Gansu government’s website yesterday.  
